FEDERAL INDUSTRIES Ltd. said it agreed with underwiters led by Scotia-McLeod Inc. to issue 75 million Canadian dollars ($63.8 million) principal amount of 9% convertible subordinated debentures.
Federal Industries, a diversified manufacturing, distribution and transportation concern based in Winnipeg, Manitoba, said the debentures will be convertible until their 1999 maturity into the company's Class A shares at C$18.50 a share.
Federal Industries said C$54 million of the proceeds will be used to finance its previously reported plan to buy W.H. Smith Canada Ltd., a bookstore chain, and the balance to repay short-term debt. 

